						               													<description>Barbershop (or Strohmann Jass) is a two player game based on the traditional game Coiffeur Jass.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the rules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Introduction&amp;#10;This is the third game in an ongoing exploration of Strawman Variations--developing two player versions of trick-taking games by adding strawmen (one or more piles of cards, usually with the top card exposed, that form part of a player&amp;rsquo;s hand).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object&amp;#10;Seventeen tricks are played each hand; certain cards are worth certain points; the object is to capture the most points. There is a small bonus for winning the last trick.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Cards&amp;#10;A pack of 36 Swiss-suited cards is used consisting of A K O U B 9 8 7 6 in four suits (acorns, bells, flowers, and shields). If you only have a pack with French suits, you can use A K Q J 10 9 8 7 6 in clubs, diamonds, hearts, and spades.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rank of the cards (and their point value) within each suit is, from highest to lowest:&amp;#10;Ace(11), King(4), Ober(3), Under(2), Banner(10), 9(0), 8(0), 7(0), 6(0).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However, when there is a trump suit, the rank (and point value) in that suit becomes: &amp;#10;Under(20), 9(14), Ace(11), King(4), Ober(3), Banner(10), 8(0), 7(0), 6(0).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With a bonus of 5 points for winning the last trick, there is a total of 157 points to capture each round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
